Visitors at Cleveland Metroparks Zoo heard a scream as the toddler tumbled into the pit at 3pm on Saturday .
Witnesses said the mother was holding the two-year-old boy and another child when he fell .
The boy suffered minor bumps and bruises and was listed in stable condition .
Zoo visitor Terra Lurie said she was 'shocked' and 'didn't understand how the parents let the kid go over the rail'